snippet.textDisplay:
First season: "he's a fraud"
Second season: Smashes nearly every record to win the league
Third season: Beats a phenomenal Liverpool side to win the league by ONE point. ( The same Liverpool that are dominating all over the place this season and won the Champion's League last season)
Fourth season: He's a fraud, he's finished, he's shaken, he's going to Juventus, he's found out that this isn't Spain or Germany...

Thing is, you know at least 80% of people commenting aren't actually doing it for banter and they genuinely don't know anything about football. I'm a United fan, hate to see City doing well, but you can't deny the man is an absolute Don.
Compare Liverpool to City since Klopp and Pep took over their teams and the comparison in trophies in embarrassing.
